newsitem.title: MALAYSIA: Malaysia end-July palm oil stocks down 2.6 pct.
newsitem.headline: Malaysia end-July palm oil stocks down 2.6 pct.

text.p: Malaysia's palm oil stocks fell 2.6 percent to 769,275 tonnes at end-July from 789,806 at end-June and compared with 755,665 at end-July 1996, the Palm Oil Registration and Licensing Authority (PORLA) said on Friday.

Stocks of crude palm oil were 426,185 tonnes, against 405,402 at end-June and 402,659 a year earlier. Processed palm oil stocks totalled 343,090 tonnes compared with 384,404 and 353,006 respectively, PORLA said.

Stocks of crude palm kernel oil were 66,115 tonnes at end-July against 53,883 at end-June and 50,357 at end-July 1996. Processed palm kernel oil stocks were 60,219 tonnes compared with 53,391 and 49,223 respectively.
